---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import bioPhoto from '../../public/images/crossed-legged.jpg'
---

<section id="bio" class="py-20 md:py-32 bg-cream-50">
  <div class="max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <h2 class="text-display text-3xl md:text-4xl text-center mb-16 scroll-reveal" data-delay="0">
      About
    </h2>

    <!-- Two-Column Layout -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-center">
      <!-- Photo Column -->
      <div class="scroll-reveal" data-delay="1">
        <Image
          src={bioPhoto}
          alt="Ross Taylor Williams seated cross-legged in natural setting"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-md shadow-md"
          loading="lazy"
          quality={85}
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Bio Text Column -->
      <div class="space-y-4 scroll-reveal" data-delay="2">
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-900">
          Ross Taylor Williams is a singer-songwriter from Los Angeles, crafting organic,
          introspective folk music that draws from the natural world and the quiet moments
          in between.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-900">
          His debut album <em>Earth Music</em> is a meditation on connection  to place, to
          memory, and to the rhythms of the earth. Recorded with minimal production and a focus
          on warmth and presence, the album invites listeners into an unhurried, contemplative space.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-cream-900">
          Ross's music has been described as "quietly powerful" and "achingly honest," blending
          fingerpicked guitar, gentle vocals, and evocative storytelling.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
